[2] Iraq
Date: 12 Feb 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: OIE Disease Information, Vol. 19, No. 6. [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/eng/info/hebdo/AIS_32.HTM#Sec0>

Avian Influenza In Iraq
--------------------------
See also: <http://www.oie.int/eng/info/hebdo/AIS_32.HTM#Sec1> 9 Feb 2006
Immediate notification report.
Information received on 3 Feb 2006 from Dr. Dawood M. Sharief,
Director General, Iraqi Veterinary Services, Ministry of Agriculture, Baghdad:

Report date: 2 Feb 2006.
Identification of agent: avian influenza virus subtype H5.
Date of 1st confirmation of the event: 1 Feb 2006.
Date of start of the event: 18 Jan 2006.
Clinical disease: yes.
Nature of diagnosis: clinical and laboratory.
Details of outbreaks:
1st administrative division: Sulaimaniyah
Lower administrative division: Raniyah
Type of epidemiological unit: village
Name of the location: Sarkapkan
Date of start of the outbreak: --
Species: avi
Number of animals in the outbreaks
susceptible / cases / deaths / destroyed* / slaughtered
1950 / 450 / 450 / 1500 / 0
1st administrative division: Sulaimaniyah
Lower administrative division: Raniyah
Type of epidemiological unit: village
Name of the location: Dawaw
Date of start of the outbreak: --
Species: avi
Number of animals in the outbreaks
susceptible / cases / deaths / destroyed* / slaughtered
1200 / 200 / 200 / 1000 / 0
* In addition, enormous numbers of poultry were destroyed in Iraqi
Kurdistan after the declaration by Turkey of confirmed occurrence of
avian influenza within the borderline.
Description of affected population: all outbreaks in poultry occurred
in backyard flocks, which generally included chickens, geese, turkeys
and ducks.
The 1st confirmed case of human bird flu in Iraq (a 15-year-old girl,
in her house, where 18 chicks died) occurred in the village of Sarkapkan.
Diagnosis:
Laboratory where diagnostic tests were performed: Central Veterinary
and Research Laboratory, Baghdad
Outbreak: Sarkapkan
Species examined: 2 chickens
Diagnostic tests used: hemagglutination inhibition test
Date: 1 Feb 2006
Results: virus subtype H5
Laboratory where diagnostic tests were performed: Central Veterinary
and Research Laboratory, Baghdad
Outbreak: Dawaw
Species examined: 2 chickens and one duck
Diagnostic tests used: hemagglutination inhibition test
Date: 1 Feb 2006
Results: virus subtype H5
Source of outbreak or origin of infection: under investigation.
Control measures:
- stamping out;
- quarantine;
- movement control inside the country;
- screening;
- zoning;
- disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s);
- dipping/spraying.
Vaccination prohibited: yes.
Final report: no.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
