Avian Influenza In Iraq
---------------------------
Follow-up report No. 1
See also:
<http://www.oie.int/eng/info/hebdo/AIS_32.HTM#Sec0> 9 Feb 2006.
Information received on 7 Feb 2006 from Dr. Dawood M. Sharief,
Director General, Iraqi Veterinary Services, Ministry of Agriculture, Baghdad:
End of previous report period: 2 Feb 2006 (see Disease Information,
19 [6], 87, dated 9 Feb 2006).
End of this report period: 7 Feb 2006.
Identification of agent: avian influenza virus subtype H5.
Date of 1st confirmation of the event: 1 Feb 2006.
Date of start of the event: 18 Jan 2006.
Clinical disease: yes.
Nature of diagnosis: clinical and laboratory.
New outbreak:
1st administrative division: Missan
Lower administrative division: Amarha
Type of epidemiological unit: village
Name of the location: Sahat Al-aradate
Date of start of the outbreak: --
Species: avi
Number of animals in the outbreak
susceptible / cases / deaths / destroyed / slaughtered
980 / 2 / 2 / 978 / 0
Description of affected population: pigeons.
Diagnosis:
Laboratory where diagnostic tests were performed: Central Veterinary
and Research Laboratory, Baghdad
Outbreak: Sahat Al-aradate
Species examined: pigeon
Diagnostic tests used: hemagglutination inhibition test
Date: 7 Feb 2006
Results: virus subtype H5
Source of outbreak or origin of infection: under investigation.
Control measures:
- stamping out;
- quarantine;
- movement control inside the country;
- screening;
- zoning;
- disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s);
- dipping/spraying.
Vaccination prohibited: yes.
Final report: no.
